  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with complex ventral hernia that are fit for surgery (ASA class I and II)
             (Saklad, 1941).

          -  Patients with class III, IV according to Pitanguy's classification of abdominal
             deformities (Pitanguy, 1995).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patient with ASA class III, IV, and V.

          2. Morbid obesity (BMI &gt; 40).

          3. Recurrent incisional hernias after mesh hernioplasty.

          4. Strangulated hernias.

          5. Isolated small paraumbilical hernias.

          6. Patients with abdominal organomegaly and/or ascites.

          7. Patients with coagulopathy,

          8. Patients who are heavy smokers, patients with pulmonary problems, and patients with
             uncontrolled diabetes.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
